{"title_page": "Anastasia Mu\u00f1oz", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name            = Anastasia Mu\u00f1oz\n| image           =\n| imagesize       =\n| alt             =\n| caption         =\n| birth_name       =\n| birth_date       =<!-- NEED SOURCE {{birth date and age|1984|05|11}} -->\n| birth_place      =\n| death_date       =\n| death_place      =\n| other_names       = Staci Moon<br>Tasia Moon\n| education       = [[University of Alabama]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://artsandculturetx.com/acting-in-texas-anastasia-munoz-time-travels-in-sarah-ruhls-orlando/|title=Acting in Texas: Anastasia Munoz Time Travels in Sarah Ruhl\u2019s Orlando|last=Wozny|first=Nancy|work=Arts and Culture Texas|date=April 3, 2014|accessdate=September 12, 2015}}</ref>\n| occupation      = Voice actress\n| years_active    = 2009\u2013present\n| status =\n| spouse          =\n| website         =\n}}\n'''Anastasia Mu\u00f1oz''' <!-- NEED SOURCE (born May 11, 1984) --> is an American voice actress affiliated with [[Funimation]]. She has provided voices for a number of English-language versions of Japanese [[anime]] films and television series. Her major characters include [[.hack//Quantum#Tobias|Tobias]] in ''[[.hack//Quantum]]'', [[List of Jormungand characters#Koko Hekmatyar|Koko Hekmatyar]] in ''[[Jormungand (manga)|Jormungand]]'', Shiena Kenmochi in ''[[Riddle Story of Devil]]'', Aria in ''[[The Sacred Blacksmith]]'', and [[List of Strike Witches characters#Minna-Dietlinde Wilcke|Minna-Dietlinde Wilcke]] in ''[[Strike Witches]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Anime===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of dubbing performances in anime\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Source<ref name=\"animecons\">{{Cite web|url=https://animecons.com/guests/bio/5596/anastasia-munoz|title=Anastasia Munoz|website=AnimeCons.com|accessdate=Jul 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Baccano!]]'' || Jacuzzi Splot (Child) || || <ref name=\"thatanimeshow\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thatanimeshow.com/?p=21|title=That Anime Show EP 5, \"Anastasia Munoz\" &#124; That Anime Show|website=www.thatanimeshow.com|accessdate=Jul 5, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Mamotte! Lollipop|Save Me! Lollipop]]'' || Forte (Young) || || <ref name=\"thatanimeshow\"/>\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood]]'' || Gracia Hughes || || <ref>{{cite episode | at=Closing credits | title=Fullmetal Alchemist | work=Funimation | episode=List of Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood episodes #Episodes list | series=Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood | serieslink=Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood | number=1 | year=2010}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010-12 || ''[[Strike Witches]]'' series || [[List of Strike Witches characters#Minna-Dietlinde Wilcke|Minna-Dietlinde Wilcke]] || || <ref>{{cite web|title=Funimation Confirms Strike Witches Cast, FMA Street Date|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-12-17/funimation-confirms-strike-witches-cast-fma-street-date|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=29 May 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Summer Wars]]'' || Yukiko Shinohara || || <ref>{{cite movie|at=Closing credits|title=Summer Wars|work=Funimation|serieslink=Summer Wars|year=2010}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[The Sacred Blacksmith]]'' || Aria || || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japanator.com/funimation-announces-cast-for-sacred-blacksmith-17656.phtml|title=FUNimation announces cast for Sacred Blacksmith|author=|date=|work=Japanator|accessdate=26 April 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2011-2013 || ''[[Baka and Test]]'' series || Hiromi Nakabayashi || || <ref>{{cite episode | at=Closing credits | title=Idiots, Classes, and a Summoning War | work=Funimation | episode=List of Baka and Test episodes | series=Baka and Test | serieslink=Baka and Test  | number=1  | year=2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Boku wa Tomodachi ga Sukunai]]'' || Asada || ||\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Ga-Rei|Ga-Rei: Zero]]'' || Ayame Jinguji || || <!-- animecons -->\n|-\n| 2011 || ''[[Rosario + Vampire]]''